CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1939, pg. 15, reads: "These Crack Swimmers Will Splash for 'Y' in Big Meet - When the A.M.A. swimming championships are held on June 23, the Center Avenue 'Y' will have two of the strongest teams in city entered. Here are the teams slated to swim for the 'Y.' ... Men's team - Bucky Washington, Jim Miles, Jack Strothers, Toby Sullivan and Coach Fountain."
TitMainTitle: Centre Avenue YMCA swim team, including Bucky Washington, Jim Miles, Jack Strothers, Toby Sullivan, and Coach Pomeroyal Fountain standing on diving board in Centre Avenue YMCA indoor swimming pool
